CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 27, 1956, pg. A1, reads: "Kiddies Meet Eleanor - A group of Addison Terrace youngsters abandoned their playtoys and games during the afternoon of Oct. 18 to know and get close to Mrs. Eleanor Roosevelt, second from left, when she dedicated a monument bought and erected for her late husband, President Franklin D. Roosevelt by tenants of Addison Terrace in 1946. Later that evening she addressed a democratic rally in Schenley High School Auditorium. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Woman standing behind table and microphone, looking towards man wearing portrait button, for dedication of monument to President Franklin Delano Roosevelt, Addison Terrace, Hill District
